357
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:18,800
Yeah, well...

358
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:22,000
So... how's domestic life?

359
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:26,100
Don't you just love being a mom?

360
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:29,300
And there it was -- the question that Lynette always dreaded.

361
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:32,400
Well, to be honest...

362
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:35,400
for those who asked it, only one answer was acceptable,

363
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:38,400
so Lynette responded as she always did.

364
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,700
She lied.

365
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:42,700
It's the best job I've ever had.

366
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:55,500
You know what I don't get?

367
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:56,500
What?

368
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:59,500
Why you married mr. Solis.

369
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,900
Well... he promised to give me everything I've ever wanted.

370
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:09,300
And did he?

371
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:12,400
Yes.

372
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:15,700
Then why aren't you happy?

373
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:19,200
Turns out I wanted all the wrong things.

374
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:23,900
So do you love him?

375
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,700
I do.

376
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:28,700
Well, then, why are we here? Why are we doing this?

377
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:31,200
Because I don't want to wake up one morning

378
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:34,200
