435
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:44,400
- I think that we should all
- Go ahead and play.

436
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:55,500
I know that you think I'm angry about coming here, but I'm not.

437
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:57,700
You and the kids wanted a change of pace,

438
00:26:57,700 --> 00:27:00,700
something fun. I get it.

439
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:03,700
Probably we'll want something healthier tomorrow night, though.

440
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:05,800
I'm thinking about chicken Saltimbocca.

441
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:08,800
I want a divorce.

442
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:13,600
I just can't live in this --

443
00:27:14,100 --> 00:27:17,100
this detergent commercial anymore.

444
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:21,300
- The salad bar's right over there. Help yourself.
- Thank you.

445
00:27:25,700 --> 00:27:28,700
Um, I think I'll go get your salad for you.

446
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:43,200
Bree Van De Kamp.

447
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:45,200
Oh. Hello, mrs. Huber.

448
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:48,200
We didn't get a chance to talk at Mary Alice's wake.

449
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:50,600
How are you doing?

450
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:54,600
Bree longed to share the truth about her husband's painful betrayal,

451
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:56,500
