556
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:25,100
You don't know what's going on.

557
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:28,100
Maybe they're just having dinner.

558
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:31,600
You're right. They're doing it.

559
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,700
Edie?

560
00:37:05,900 --> 00:37:07,600
Anybody home?

561
00:37:10,700 --> 00:37:13,700
I need to borrow sugar.

562
00:37:34,500 --> 00:37:37,600
And just like that, the possibility Susan had clung to,

563
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:41,600
the maybe of Mike Delfino, was gone forever.

564
00:37:45,100 --> 00:37:48,100
And despite the precariousness of her situation,

565
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:51,100
Susan took a moment to mourn her loss.

566
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:23,000
It didn't take Susan long to realize this was just not her night.

567
00:38:24,300 --> 00:38:27,400
Is somebody out there?

568
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:28,900
Oh, my god!

569
00:38:28,900 --> 00:38:29,900
That's smoke!

570
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:50,200
