571
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:53,300
Paramedics said she was lucky. She could have been killed.

572
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:56,000
She ran out with nothing on.

573
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:59,000
She was having sex with some guy when the fire started.

574
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:00,300
What happened to him?

575
00:39:00,300 --> 00:39:03,300
He got smoke inhalation. He's at the hospital.

576
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:07,600
Susan, are you all right? You look awful.

577
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:09,600
I'm fine. I'm fine.

578
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:13,600
I-I just, uh... feel really bad for Edie.

579
00:39:14,400 --> 00:39:17,400
Oh, honey, don't worry about Edie. She's a strong lady.

580
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:19,400
Absolutely. She'll get through this.

581
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,400
She'll find a way to survive.

582
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:24,400
We all do.

583
00:39:26,700 --> 00:39:28,700
Come on.

584
00:39:46,300 --> 00:39:48,100
Wow, what happened?

585
00:39:48,100 --> 00:39:48,800
Mike.

586
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:50,900
And suddenly, there he was,

587
00:39:50,900 --> 00:39:53,300
like a phoenix rising from the ashes.

588
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:56,200
I-I thought you were --

589
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:57,400
Uh, where were you?

590
00:39:57,400 --> 00:40:00,400
I just got back from the movies. Edie had a fire, huh?

591
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,700
Yeah.

592
00:40:02,700 --> 00:40:05,700
Yeah, but she's fine now.

593
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:08,500
Everything's fine now.

594
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:11,200
